The video website has been blocked after voice recordings of senior officials discussing a potential military operation in Syria have flooded the site - it  is believed.

Government officials confirmed today that more social media platforms could be blocked if national security was threatened.

At a rally today, the Prime Minister described the fact that the audio had been posted on Youtube as 'villainous'.

A source at the Prime Minister, Recep Tayyip Erdogan's office said today that the videos had caused 'a national security issue'.

The source said that Turkey was in talks with the video sharing platform and may lift the ban if YouTube agreed to remove the content.

